07/10/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The government adopted on Monday (6 October) a draft law on citizenship that reduces the minimum period of residence from 15 years to eight years.
The draft also revises conditions for acquiring citizenship by foreigners married to Macedonian citizens, as well as those with refugee status.
The law was drafted after consultations with the main political parties and in line with EU requirements.
(MIA, A1 TV - 06/10/03)
